{
  "stem": "964.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We read in the-- we read in the papers that it was going on in Germany when the Nazis came to power.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But, you know, paper.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But since they dropped these people over the border into Poland, and they start coming to our town, the kehilla, the Jewish committee, start to settle them, gave them apartments and buy them furniture, all these things.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then we heard directly from them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Then we got the picture.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You see, Jewish history is full of programs, full of catastrophes.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You take-- go back to the Spanish Inquisition.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You go back when the Romans-- when the Romans conquer Israel, they disperse the Jews.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Jews came into Rome and, and, and, and lived in ghettos.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So all through our history we used to.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But we, we never thought that it would come to a point that Jewish-- taking people in concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We thought, all right, he's crazy.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So he dropped all-- sent back the Polish citizens back to Poland.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we all-- as I told you, my sister left.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We-- my oldest brother tried to go to, to Stock-- to Sweden.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But he didn't have the money to go to Sweden.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He wanted to go to Sweden.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then with Sweden, he thinks that he go to, to the United States, but there was no way.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Even if you had the money, you couldn't.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It, it-- nobody would give you a visa.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The Germans Jews, I heard, and I know from way back, somehow-- because probably there, there were rich people that had the money so they could buy themselves a visa, or deposit some money so that they were allowed to come in to America, to, to Argentina, to other countries.",
      "word_count": 50
    }
  ],
